<section class="help-card help-card--city">
  <div class="help-card__eyebrow">Local guidance</div>
  <h2 class="help-card__title">
    How to think about leasing space in {{ city.city }}, {{ city.state_abbr }}
  </h2>

  <p class="help-card__intro">
    Finding the right space comes down to balancing location, budget, layout, and timing.
    In {{ city.city }}, it helps to start with your use case, then compare neighborhoods,
    accessibility, and total occupancy cost.
  </p>

  <div class="help-card__grid">
    <div class="help-card__item">
      <h3>Start with your use</h3>
      <p>
        Office, retail, industrial, and flex users all have different needs.
        Clarify team size, customer access, parking, and workflow before touring.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="help-card__item">
      <h3>Budget beyond base rent</h3>
      <p>
        Total cost often includes CAM/NNN, utilities, deposits, insurance,
        and improvements—not just advertised rent.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="help-card__item">
      <h3>Plan your timing</h3>
      <p>
        Searching, touring, negotiation, and move-in can take longer than expected—
        especially if buildout or permits are involved.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="help-card__item">
      <h3>Compare neighborhoods</h3>
      <p>
        The right block often matters more than the building. Look at foot traffic,
        access, nearby businesses, and how the area fits your brand.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>